m of doing with my EQ rogue. Only wish I could have more time to play. But yes, I will agree a bit of work needs to be done to get us where we thought we would be as far as the description for rogue classes were presented on the box. <p>Perdus Brewslayer Lvl 56 Halfling rogue of RN <BR>
Midgardian Shadowblade of Kay/Galahad server. </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usugoi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sugoi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.planetunreal.com/images/camper.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/15/01 5:04:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urunetheborrower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rune the Borrower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/01 4:05:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: thIEf walk-out</span><hr size=1> I don't think a few posts about how incontent we are with the way things have been going should get those of you who feel great about the Assassans of DAoC so upset. I feel that the posts here are much more subdued than they were in the Main Lounge 30 months ago. I know people were talking a walkout on more than one occasion then. Now I don't see anyone talking about atttempting to bring the servers down, they did then.<br>
<br>
I feel that the main thing that has folks so antsy now is the thing that drew us to DAoC. The ability to &quot;spec&quot; your rogue to be YOUR rogue. I'm shure that's what brought many of us here. The chance to NOT be a &quot;cookie-cut rouge&quot;. (Spelled that way on porpose.)<br>
<br>
In DAoC, what is createing the &quot;pucker factor&quot; around here, is the fact that if points are spent wrong you can end up with something that, if not gimped, can still be a far cry from what you thought you were going to get.<br>
<br>
So many of us are getting or have gotten to points of no return with our templates and, untill 2 days ago, Mythic hasn't told us ANYTHING about how our spec lines were going to turn out. Hell, if they had told us about what they were doing with the various dual wield styles (Not just a rogue issue) it would've helped.<br>
<br>
I played a couple months of AO &quot;between&quot; EQ and DAoC. The main reason I left that game was because of the lack of communication between Funcom and their customer base. Mythic was beginning to look a lot like Funcom to me.<br>
<br>
I have to agree with Dowser and the others that say Mythic's approach is like they either never wrote up a plan for what the Assassans were supposed to be or they filed it somplace and forgot where they put it. I remember Remmi stating that who ever was doing poisons was doing it in their free time because they were working on something else full time. This person that was working on a &quot;defining&quot; part of our skill set had as his actual job something like dungeon itemizing or quests and wasn't even working on classes at all.<br>
<br>
This leads me to picture people in 4 or 5 different departments working on various parts of our class in their spare time and with little, if any, communication with each other on where they were headed and how it would all mesh together in the end. It's obvious to me that there is no &quot;team lead&quot; for the Assassans (and probably Archers) by the way some patches have indirectly &quot;nerfed&quot; us in ways that a competent &quot;lead&quot; would've noticed before it went in.<br>
<br>
